q15.value:
1. Anticipated start date: 02/14/2020;

2. Anticipated completion date: 05/20/2020;

3. Participants/population: Patients with diagnosed IBS will be included, regardless of gender, age, race, education status, cases of source and different subtypes of IBS.

4. Intervention(s), exposure(s): Intervention measures will be either acupoint catgut embedding alone or combined with other methods.

5. Comparator(s)/control: Fake acupoint catgut embedding, normal acupuncture, western medicine, fire needle acupuncture, auricular point therapy, blank control, placebo control and other interventions. Interventions in the experimental group were not included.

6. Types of study to be included: We will include randomised controlled trials (RCTs), published and unpublished, in English and Chinese.

